Description:
Master Your Destiny
Desirably close to buzzing Sydney Road restaurants, shops and transport, this spacious double fronted, two bedroom home delivers fantastic versatility and a myriad of options. Nestled on approximately 401m2, immediately comfortable whilst offering broad appeal for those looking to enhance, extend, start fresh or develop, (STCA). Comprising a street facing lounge that flows through the central dining room, a sizeable kitchen/meals with gas stove, an abundance of cupboards and counter space, it also features a light filled sunroom. The two double bedrooms come with built-in robes and share a neat bathroom with a shower and vanity, while further features include heating, evaporative cooling, high ceilings, a rear yard, long side driveway and a deep garage. With so many possibilities rolling out before you, this is an excellent opportunity to seize the reins and shape the future to match your desires (subject to relevant approvals).

Time To Shine
So close to everything, this distinctive three bedroom home offers spacious rooms, lofty ceilings and lots of scope for inspired buyers looking to really make a home their own, creating a welcoming base in an increasingly sought after locale. Presenting a front garden graced with colourful roses, overlooked by the street facing living room with heating and cooling, kitchen and meals domain with gas stove and rear garden ready for transformation. Description:
Landmark Victorian with an Extravagant Extension
One of the area's finest homes, this freestanding balconied terrace delivers an inner-urban lifestyle of unrivalled luxury and family flexibility with its extended floorplan, first-class features and prime location just north of Brunswick's border. Beyond its gorgeous Hawthorn-brick facade, the home's equally-alluring interior boasts four bedrooms (extra-large upstairs master with retreat/dressing room, deluxe ensuite and private balcony), main bathroom with spa and guest powder room (third WC). Add to this an elegant lounge (including retractable projector screen and integrated speakers), formal dining and additional living area complemented by a gourmet granite-bench kitchen with breakfast bar, walk-in pantry, Neff dual ovens and integrated dishwasher. Other highlights include ducted heating and refrigerated cooling (zoned), ducted vacuum, security system, data cabling throughout, excellent storage spaces, large laundry with chute, ornate ceilings and polished timber floors, plus bi-folds to a wonderfully private entertainers' courtyard, internally-accessed double garage (r/c) via ROW. Walking distance to Moreland Station and Sydney Road trams, Upfield Bike Path, cool cafes, renowned restaurants and an endless array of boutique shops. Absolutely one of a kind!
Insights: 42a Cameron Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Come Home To The Grove
Take your place in The Grove by becoming the proud owner of this two bedroom villa unit and you'll soon see why it's often regarded as Coburg's finest street. Walk under broad leafy canopies from the tram to the door and step inside to discover an entrance area and comfortable living room, kitchen/meals and courtyard. An electric stove meets with a pantry, cupboards and tiled splashbacks in the kitchen, naturally bright double bedrooms come with built-in robes, and in the central bathroom/laundry you'll find a bath, shower, toilet and vanity. Polished floorboards and Panasonic inverter heating and cooling enhance comfort and appeal, and with a little work the courtyard could become an inviting place to relax. Immediately liveable with great enhancement potential, this elevated home is just a short stroll to Nicholson Street trams, and easy walking distance to Merri Creek and the restaurants, cafes, shops, bars and trams of cosmopolitan Sydney Road.
Insights: 3/78 The Grove, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 73 other 2 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Stunning City Fringe Charmer
Immaculately restored three bedroom plus study, two bathroom city fringe dwelling flaunts exceptional character appeal while delivering on every modern convenience for a luxurious lifestyle. Comprising lounge, dining, kitchen showcasing stone benchtops, soft-close cabinetry/drawers, stainless steel dishwasher, 900mm gas stove/electric oven and fridge water connection; stepping to undercover alfresco with tumbled brick pavers set in landscaped gardens. All bedrooms include mirrored built-in robes and are serviced by two bathrooms; central bathroom with double stone vanity and bath. Freestanding studio with kitchenette takes advantage of private access via side driveway to rear. Features solid hardwood floors, ducted heating, 2 split systems, alarm, automatic gate to side drive and OSP, 4.4KW solar panels, water tank, garden shed, workshop. Enviably located close to shops, buses, trains, trams, and schools.

Description:
Size Surprise In A Lifestyle Locale
Behind a sweet facade and classic picket fence sits a deceptively spacious three bedroom home, enviably positioned to offer a lifestyle of absolute convenience.
Updated to reflect a clean modern aesthetic while enjoying the gracious proportions and high ceilings of our Edwardian heritage, this generous residence offers a timeless and versatile floor plan. A long entrance hall introduces three double bedrooms, one equally comfortable as a second living area or substantial study, before giving way to the spacious open plan living domain.
Bright and airy, the stylish kitchen features Omega appliances, dishwasher and walk-in-pantry, flowing to a deck and cottage inspired rear garden setting the scene for an effortless indoor-outdoor lifestyle.
Add to this a bright central bathroom, separate laundry, panel and gas heating, ceiling fans and off-street parking.
Nestled in a prized location, a short walk to cosmopolitan Sydney Road specialty shopping and cafes, Merri Creek parklands and trails, schools and choice of city-bound tramlines, this tidy home will appeal to young families, market entrants and downsizers.

Description:
Family sanctuary on great allotment
The Australian dream lives on in this quiet tree lined street where family living and friendly neighbours provide for a relaxed and tranquil lifestyle.
This traditional family home is floodlit with an abundance of natural light and is sited on a beautiful garden allotment of some 437SqM, where the fully established fruit trees, shrubs and organic veggie garden are all easily maintained from the 3000 litre water tank.
Accommodation comprises 3 large bedrooms, spacious formal lounge room, and open plan kitchen/dining area, ideal for entertaining.
Features include Baltic timber flooring, original fretwork and ornate ceilings, hydronic heating, air conditioning, side driveway, and workshop with studio for the budding artisan or possible additional accommodation. Covered front and rear timber decking along with built in BBQ and pizza oven offer outdoor entertainment options for summer parties.
City bound trams and Batman train station are less than 200m away and convenient shopping options are a breeze with Gaffney St Shopping precinct only 500m away.
In conjunction with Elite Real Estate - Vince Sinni 0423 551 888

Description:
Parkland Paradise
Part of the Merriview Place complex of select apartments and terraced residences, this modern three bedroom home offers an exceptional inner urban lifestyle. Overlooking delightful Merri Creek and boasting direct access to its surrounding parklands and trails, this serenely positioned property delivers a lifestyle of absolute convenience with the benefits of proximity to Sydney Road trams, specialty shopping, choice of schools and Farmers Markets ready to service all your lifestyle needs. Quality built over two sundrenched levels this spacious home features a contemporary open plan that showcases a gourmet stone topped kitchen boasting stainless steel 900mm cooking, dishwasher and classy glass tile splashbacks. Opening to an easy care courtyard that in turn opens to a large double garage via sliding glass doors, effortlessly doubling the outdoor area, it offers the ultimate in seamless indoor-outdoor entertaining. Take advantage of the communal pool and BBQ facilities, a further bonus for your summer entertaining needs. Double bedrooms with BIR’s are serviced by two well appointed bathrooms, master with ensuite, while comfort and security are assured with a separate laundry, copious internal storage, split system heating/cooling throughout and secure, remote gated entry to double garage. Ready to enjoy, inspection will impress.
Features
- Modern three bedroom residence boasts direct access to Merri Creek parklands, trails
- Open plan living, gourmet Caesar Stone kitchen boasting 900mm cooking, dishwasher
- Clever courtyard opens to the double garage creating a sizeable entertaining domain
- Access to an in-ground pool and BBQ facilities offer exceptional summer entertaining
- Bright bedrooms with BIR’s, two stylish bathrooms, master with ensuite and WIR
- Split system heating/cooling throughout, secure and private entry to the double garage

Description:
A New Beginning Beckons
Ideally positioned within walking distance to Batman Train Station, Coburg North Primary School and Upfield Bike Path, this spacious three bedroom home is certainly placed for convenience and lifestyle enjoyment.
The floor plan incorporates rooms of generous proportions framed by high ceilings.
Three huge bedrooms introduce the home with living zones following at the rear, namely the kitchen/meals area and family room.
There's also a central bathroom, covered outdoor area, a separate laundry, old fashioned outhouse (second toilet) as well as evaporative air conditioning and electronic security shutters throughout plus off street parking at the front.
The home presents an excellent opportunity for renovators to restore and modernise with options to extend either outwards or upwards, both subject to council approval.
Alternatively, a great parcel of land in ever popular Coburg offers an exciting canvas upon which to design and build that elusive dream home (once again STCA).
Further enticement is generated by close proximity to iconic O'Heas Bakery, Coburg Shopping Centre, Sydney Road's cosmopolitan mix of shops and eateries, CityLink and beautiful Coburg Lake Reserve.

Description:
A Sensational Start
An outstanding opportunity for first home buyers, professional couples or investors, this 1-BR apartment offers A crisp modern interior and clever design enhance the starter and investor appeal of this stylish studio apartment. Part of The Nicholson complex this sophisticated apartment features a stylishly appointed modern kitchen, with chic two tone cabinetry, stone benchtops and quality stainless steel appliances including dishwasher. A generous bathroom features an oversized shower and elegant stone shelving while built in storage cleverly incorporates a Euro laundry for your convenience. An onsite supermarket, secure video entry, storage cage, secure car parking available, lift access and split system heating/cooling guaranteeing security, comfort and convenience. Boasting outstanding proximity to bustling Sydney Road specialty shopping, Merri Creek parklands, immediate tram access where a short trip finds iconic Lygon Street restaurants and bars and the CBD.

Description:
Location, Potential and 20m Frontage!
Instantly appealing with its immaculate interior and large rooms, this single-level home occupies one of Coburg's larger blocks (approx 700sqm) offering a world of opportunities for those looking to renovate, rebuild or completely redevelop (STCA). Enjoyed by the one family since new (c1978), the home's current floorplan comprises three spacious bedrooms, modern central bathroom and separate WC, light-filled lounge and dining through to the kitchen/meals area. Other features include ducted heating throughout, a/c (dining room), large laundry and security shutters all-round, plus undercover patio overlooking an expansive backyard complete with garage via gated side driveway. Moments from local buses and Nicholson Street trams, it's also walking distance to local schools, Merri Creek trails and parkland, as well as easy access to Coburg Shopping Centre and Coburg Station. Just imagine the possibilities!
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING: Wednesday 22nd November at 5pm
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Affordable entry to central Coburg!
This wonderful three bedroom home has been updated and is ready to move into now. Situated a few minutes stroll to Central Coburg shopping, Coburg Rail Station and Sydney Road tram, this home is in a great location that is close to schools, Coburg Lake and Pentridge Village.
Accommodation Includes:
• Formal entrance hallway
• Spacious formal lounge room
• Updated kitchen with meals area, stone benchtops, Gas cooking and dishwasher
• Sizeable master bedroom with walk in robe and full ensuite bathroom
• Two more spacious bedrooms (one with BIR)
• Central bathroom with separate shower and bathtub
• Separate W/C
• Full sized laundry
• Wide side drive
Featuring: Gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling, polished timber floors throughout, dishwasher and covered entertaining at rear.
The perfect home for first home buyers, downsizers who want to stay in the area or investors that are looking for a quality home in a central location with no money to spend.
